OccurrenceNote:
Northern Pike were confirmed in Stormy Lake in 2001.  A northern pike eradication project at Stormy Lake in starting in fall 2012 was successful, removing the only known population of northern pike from Kenai National Wildlife Refuge.

In spring 2019 northern pike were found in Vogel Lake.
